                           <item>ጽ፡, ጽዋ፡ for ጽዋዕ፡</item>
                           <item>ኅ፡, ኅብ፡ for ዘኅብስተ፡</item>
                           <item>ግዕ፡ for ግዕዝ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; elements of the punctuation signs,
                           Ethiopic numerals or their elements.
 Text I
 Groups of lines
                           (alternating with black lines) in the incipit page; names of antiphons
                           (mawāśǝʾt) followed by feast names; numbers of psalms; names of sections
                           of antiphons and their abbreviations (mǝlṭān and mazmur); chains of black
                           and red dots separating antiphones.
 Text II
 Groups of lines
                           (alternating with black lines) in the incipit page; names of sections
                           (zǝmmāre) followed by feast or day names; names of subsections and their
                           abbreviations (ḫǝbǝst, Manfas, ṣǝwwaʿ) followed by feast names and
                           occasionally by the date of the feast; musical notation: intratextual
                           signs, interlinear signs (e.g., fols. 40rc, 43vab, 45rbc, 48rbc, 48v,
                           61ra, 70r, 101rv) and elements of marginal signs.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
